L=(\partial_\mu \phi^*)(\partial^\mu \phi)-m^2|\phi|^2
(+---)
L=(\partial_t \phi^*)(\partial_t \phi)-\nabla\phi^*\cdot \nabla \phi -m^2|\phi|^2
\phi=\exp(-imt)\tilde{\phi}
\partial_t \phi=\exp(-imt)(-im\tilde{\phi}+\partial_t \tilde{\phi})
(\partial_t \phi^*)(\partial_t \phi)=m^2|\phi|^2+im[(\partial_t \tilde{\phi})\tilde{\phi}^*-(\partial_t \tilde{\phi}^*)\tilde{\phi}]+\textrm{terms in second order in }\partial_t \textrm{which can be ignored in non-relativistic limit}
\nabla\phi^*\cdot \nabla \phi=\nabla\tilde{\phi}^*\cdot \nabla \tilde{\phi}
L=im[(\partial_t \tilde{\phi})\tilde{\phi}^*-(\partial_t \tilde{\phi}^*)\tilde{\phi}]-\nabla\tilde{\phi}^*\cdot \nabla \tilde{\phi}
(\partial_t \tilde{\phi})\tilde{\phi}^*-(\partial_t \tilde{\phi}^*)\tilde{\phi}=2(\partial_t \tilde{\phi})\tilde{\phi}^*
